SIMPLE: gustable
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gustable
<hw>Gust"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Gust</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of
being tasted; tastable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This position informs us of a vulgar error, terming the gall⟦br⟧
bitter; whereas there is nothing <qex>gustable</qex> sweeter.</q>
<rj><qau>Harvey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pleasant to the taste; toothsome; savory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>gustable</qex> thing, seen or smelt, excites the appetite,
and affects the glands and parts of the mouth.</q>
<rj><qau>Derham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gustable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gustable
<hw>Gust"a*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything that can be
tasted.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gustard</ent>⟦br⟧
